RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR GROUNDS RACE 1 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 61. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since December 19 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Louisiana Bred NW2 $5000 & NW3 $5000 Not Considered In Eligib ility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HONORARY GUEST settled off of the pace along the inside, moved to a two wide tracking position down the backstretch, pursued from the three path around the far turn before tipping to the five path to be outside of the newly clear leader in upper stretch, ranged up to bid at the furlong grounds, forged an advantage at the sixteenth pole, and drew clear. HAPPY SAILS tracked in the four to five path around the first turn, pressed the top pair into the far turn, was roused to bid from the four path with three furlongs to go, drove past the leaders turning for home, drew clear entering the lane, but met an outer bid in midstretch, got headed at the sixteenth pole, and gave way. MAGICAL STARDUST tracked along the inside, but was shuffled back behind a weakening rival turning for home, tipped three wide entering the lane, claimed show in upper stretch, and chased the top pair home. MEG AND CLAIR trailed around both turns, shifted to the six path in upper stretch, and moved up. FIBRILLATOR bobbled slightly a stride out after the start, vied for the lead in the five to four path around the first turn, vied with an inner rival entering the backstretch, led in the three path into the far turn, but was outkicked by an outer rival turning for home, weakened through the lane, and was vanned off. LAKE RUNNER vied for the lead inside of a rival while in the three path around the first turn, then from the two path into the far turn, but failed to keep pace with an outer pair at the three furlong pole, and weakened turning for home.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR GROUNDS RACE 2 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 92. Starter Allowance Purse 30000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $50,000 OR LESS AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING OR WAIVER CLAIMING. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since December 19 Allowed 3 lbs. (Races Where E ntered For $25,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COUSIN LARRY settled off of the pace along the inside, gained place from outer rivals into the far turn, narrowed the run-away leader's clear margin around that bend, tipped outside of him to take aim in upper stretch, ranged up nearing the furlong grounds, but drifted out from a left handed crop leaving that station, sustained stride and produced a bid while changing back to his right lead at the sixteenth pole, then dueled through the closing stages, and narrowly prevailed. MASTER GAME tugged in the bit while vying inside of a rival and a bit off of the rail around the first turn, pulled away while remaining keyed up under tight restraint entering the backstretch, settled into stride around the far turn as his advantage narrowed, held sway through upper stretch, flopped back to his left lead inside the final furlong as an outer rival menaced, dueled gamely with that foe through the late stages, but was nailed at the wire. KEEPCALMCARRYON rated at the rear two wide, was urged along in the five path around the far turn, and moved up. REWIRE stalked outside of the keyed up leader and from the three path around the first turn, came into the backstretch in the five path, then gave way in the four path around the far turn, weakened between horses entering the lane, yet darted out to the center of the track at the furlong grounds. CARTIER CAT tracked in the three path, but was tentative to secure position between horses at the nine sixteenths pole, trailed in the two path into the far turn, and made little impact.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR GROUNDS RACE 3 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 95. Claiming Purse 24000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES OVER A MILE SINCE JULY 19, 2022. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since December 19 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000 (Races Where En tered For $10,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SMOKEY HARBOR prompted the pace in the four to three path into the first turn, vied two wide leaving it, opened up under rider's urging in the three path into the far turn, maintained a clear margin through midstretch, but drifted out while tiring approaching the final sixteenth, balked crossing over the leftover dirt marks from the starting gate causing him to flop leads, yet held from an inner re-bidder. BOOTDADDY JUSTICE vied along the inside of the eventual winner, yielded to that foe entering the far turn, dug in for place turning for home, yet regained stride in upper stretch, stayed on to attempt a re-bid inside of the wandering leader in the late stages, but did not have enough. OTTOTHELEGEND stalked the leading pair three wide and between horses, but came under a stern drive at the three furlong pole, and kept on mildly. DUKE OF CARTHANIA tracked four wide, gained into the far turn to vie for place at the five sixteenths pole, but flattened out. PALATIAL TIMES laid off of the pace while hung five wide around the first turn, then trailed around the far turn, and failed to factor. SIERRA HOTEL saved ground while stalking the leaders, but faded.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR GROUNDS RACE 4 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 80. Maiden Claiming Purse 28000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $50,000 (Preference To Horses That Have Not Started For Less Than $30,000 In Their Last 3 Starts).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HUNTER'S DRIVE bumped with an inner rival at the start, then checked when put to tight quarters three wide and among foes at the back of the pack into the first turn, settled off of the pace four wide, but failed to respond while getting outkicked by an inner rival turning for home, cut the corner entering the lane, rallied along the rail to bid leaving upper stretch, led entering the final furlong, and held from an outer chaser thereafter. SOFT PANTS stalked along the inside, shifted to the four path at the five sixteenths pole to split the leading trio three wide entering the lane, bid in upper stretch, but was outkicked by an inner rival at the furlong grounds, then chased that foe home well. WOLF HUNTER raced in midpack along the inside, but was wrestled back under very stout restraint around the first turn, saved ground well back around the far turn, fanned to the six path entering the lane, and stayed on. Z Z'S PRINCE stalked three to two wide around the first turn, vied between horses entering the far turn, but yielded at the furlong gounds. MINNESOTA MOON bumped with an outer rival at the start, lacked speed four wide, inched forward entering the backstretch, sustained progress to vie for the lead three wide nearing the far turn, sparred in the four path around that turn, but weakened after being floated to the five path approaching the lane. BOXSTER set the pace, vied inside of a pair of bidders entering the far turn, but was headed around that bend, then weakened between horses in upper stretch. COTE D'IVOIRE laid off of the pace two wide and between horses while tugging around the first turn, and was done early.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: NOSILVERSPOONSHERE set the pace, approaching the five furlong pole, opened up on her own power around the far turn, and widened handily. LEAD ME laid off of the pace in the three path, gained inside of foes entering the far turn to gain place with three furlongs to go, then failed to threaten the leader while safely managing that position thereafter. UNIFIED LOVE bumped an inner rival at the start, trailed along the inside, gained ground along the fence around the far turn, achieved show turning for home, and leveled off. KITTENOFTHE COURT bumped an outer rival at the start, stalked along the inside, but faded three wide around the far turn. CLASSICAL MAGNOLIA bobbled inwardly at the start, tracked from the three path, but gave way while hung five wide around the far turn. ROCKETT MAGIC took bumps from rivals on either side at the start, pressed the leader from the outside, but failed to keep pace entering the backstretch, and weakened four wide into the far turn.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR GROUNDS RACE 6 1 1/16M Turf CR: 87. Allowance Purse 51000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, WAIVER CLAIMING, STARTER OR STATE BRED ALLOWANCE OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races At A Mile Or Over On Th e Turf Since November 19 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since Then Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $40,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) (Preference To Horses That Have Not Started For Less Than $40,000 In Their Last 3 Starts). (If deemed inad visable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile and One Sixteenth.) (Rail at 34 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KATHAAN rated off of the pace two wide, moved forward between horses turning for home, rallied on his left lead while shifting outside of the embattled leading pair in upper stretch, changed over while taking aim entering the final furlong, and offered a good kick to drive past them a sixteenth from home. LOLLOPING popped open the gate pre-race causing restlessness for most of the field, established a loose margin in the two path into the first turn, dug in to resist WAYWARDNESS's bid turning for home, quickly recovered from a light brush to her hind quarters in upper stretch, gamely sparred while clinging to an advantage through midstretch, but was outkicked by an outer oncharging foe in the final sixteenth. WAYWARDNESS stalked outside of the clear leader and from the four path, bid turning for home, dueled through midstretch while not able to reach even terms, but was outkicked by an outer bidder while flopping back to her left lead, and was fended off for place. LIVY B took brushes from rivals on either side while off a step slow, raced at the rear along the inside, gained inside of the eventual winner to bid for show turning for home, but failed go rally along with that one in upper stretch, and chased. LADY EMILY tracked along the inside, but yielded in the five path around the far turn. FORDLAND tracked in the five path around the first turn, but faded entering the far one.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROSE PALACE dueled for the lead inside of a rival while remaining a bit off of the inner rail, shook free of that foe in upper stretch, and held sway from her through the final furlong. PLEASE BE KIND vied for the lead outside of the eventual winner while kept in the three path, but failed to keep pace in upper stretch, and chased her home well through the final furlong. CATWINGS tracked in the three path, tipped out to the five path entering the turn, gained show turning for home, but leveled off without threatening the top two, and managed show through the final furlong. LADY HUXLEY laid off of the pace in the two path, then chased from between horses through the lane. PARKER EVA tracked along the inside, but lacked a bid. CHEEKY pursued from midpack in the four path, but yielded entering the turn. I AM UP prompted the pace outside of the top two, but weakened around the turn. PERFECTION SAVER was outrun.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR GROUNDS RACE 8 6F Dirt CR: 73. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE JULY 19, 2022. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since December 19 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Races W here Entered For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility And Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FOR REAL ALICE tracked in the two path, chased before tipping to the five path entering the lane, offered a grinding charge to bid at the sixteenth pole, led shortly after, and held. THEBOYZGALAXY broke out, raced far back in the two path, swung to the nine path in upper stretch, and rallied on his left lead to reach place late. POINT OF VICTORY pressed two wide and between horses, but failed to keep pace with the leader entering the lane before being brushed to the four path by an inner rival at the quarter pole, yet sustained vying position among foes nearing the final sixteenth, but was outkicked late, and caught at the wire for place. A. K. A. GRAMS broke a step slow while last away, stalked along the inside, brushed his way to the three path to be outside of the clear leader leaving the quarter pole, bid at the furlong grounds, led shortly after, but faltered between bidders in the final sixteenth. NEW YEAR'S PARTY laid off of the pace along the inside, but steadied entering the turn, closed the gap behind the main group through midstretch, offered a three wide foe-splitting charge in the final sixteenth, but ran out of ground. PEACEFUL VISION laid off of the pace, tucked to the rail entering the turn, then chased along it through the lane. SHADES OF TRUTH shook her head at the start, set the pace along the inside, shook free of a pressing foe entering the lane, but was headed approaching the final sixteenth, and faltered between horses. STORIED TRIP raced far back in the four path, then failed to menace in the eight path. HALFGLAMOROUS tracked three wide, but bore out to be six wide entering the lane, and weakened.
